author: Mao Zongwu
notes: 毛宗武 / Mao Zongwu. 优诺语研究 / Younuo yu yan jiu (A Study of Younuo). Beijing: 民族出版社 / Min zu chu ban she, 2007.ISO 639-3: buh. Mao (2007) describes 2 dialects, Xiaozhai (小寨) and Huangluo (黄落), which are both spoken in Longsheng County (龙胜县), Guangxi, China. There is little variation between the two dialects. The one used here is the Xiaozhai dialect.The Xiaozhai Younuo tones are:1 = /33/2 = /13/3 = /22/4 = /22/5 = /35/6 = /31/7 = /53/8 = /31/
